# Cursor AI Rules for YouTube Playlist Project

## Issue Tracking with bd (beads)

**CRITICAL**: This project uses **bd (beads)** for ALL task tracking. Do NOT create markdown TODO lists or use other tracking methods.

### Before Starting Any Work

1. Check for ready work: `bd ready --json`
2. Claim the task: `bd update <id> --status in_progress`
3. Work on the implementation
4. If you discover new work, create linked issues: `bd create "Found bug" -p 1 --deps discovered-from:<parent-id> --json`
5. When done, close the task: `bd close <id> --reason "Done" --json`

### Essential Commands

```bash
# Find work to do
bd ready --json                           # Show unblocked issues

# Create issues
bd create "Title" -t bug|feature|task -p 0-4 --json
bd create "Subtask" --parent <epic-id> --json

# Update issues  
bd update <id> --status in_progress --json
bd update <id> --priority 1 --json

# Complete work
bd close <id> --reason "Completed" --json

# Always sync at end of session
bd sync
```

### Issue Types & Priorities

**Types**: `bug`, `feature`, `task`, `epic`, `chore`

**Priorities**:
- `0` - Critical (security, data loss, broken functionality)
- `1` - High (major features, important bugs)
- `2` - Medium (default, nice-to-have)
- `3` - Low (polish, optimization)  
- `4` - Backlog (future ideas)

### AI Planning Documents

Store ALL planning/design documents in `history/` directory:
- PLAN.md, DESIGN.md, IMPLEMENTATION.md
- ARCHITECTURE.md, TESTING_GUIDE.md
- Any other ephemeral planning files

**Keep the repository root clean!**

### Important Rules

✅ **DO**:
- Use `bd` for ALL task tracking
- Always use `--json` flag for programmatic commands
- Check `bd ready` before asking "what should I work on?"
- Link discovered work with `discovered-from` dependencies
- Store planning docs in `history/` directory
- Run `bd <cmd> --help` to discover available flags
- Commit `.beads/issues.jsonl` with code changes

❌ **DO NOT**:
- Create markdown TODO lists
- Use external issue trackers
- Duplicate tracking systems
- Clutter repo root with planning documents
- Commit `.beads/beads.db` (only JSONL)

### Project-Specific Guidelines

- **Tech Stack**: Pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript (no frameworks)
- **APIs**: YouTube Data API v3, YouTube IFrame API
- **Testing**: Test in browser before committing
- **Mobile**: Ensure responsive design

### Git Integration

Git hooks automatically sync bd issues:
- **post-commit**: Auto-exports to JSONL
- **post-merge**: Auto-imports from JSONL  
- **post-checkout**: Auto-syncs on branch switches

